# Firebase Authentication

Firebase Auth provides backend services, SDKs, and ready-made UI libraries to authenticate users. It supports email/password, phone, OAuth providers, anonymous accounts, and custom tokens.

## Email/Password Sign-Up

```typescript
import { getAuth, createUserWithEmailAndPassword } from 'firebase/auth';

const auth = getAuth();
const { user } = await createUserWithEmailAndPassword(
  auth,
  'user@example.com',
  'securepassword123'
);
console.log('Created user:', user.uid);
```

## Email/Password Sign-In

```typescript
import { signInWithEmailAndPassword } from 'firebase/auth';

const { user } = await signInWithEmailAndPassword(
  auth,
  'user@example.com',
  'securepassword123'
);
console.log('Signed in:', user.email);
```

## Google OAuth with signInWithPopup

```typescript
import { signInWithPopup, GoogleAuthProvider } from 'firebase/auth';

const provider = new GoogleAuthProvider();
provider.addScope('email');
provider.addScope('profile');

const result = await signInWithPopup(auth, provider);
const credential = GoogleAuthProvider.credentialFromResult(result);
const accessToken = credential?.accessToken;
console.log('Google user:', result.user.displayName);
```

## Phone Auth

```typescript
import { signInWithPhoneNumber, RecaptchaVerifier } from 'firebase/auth';

// Set up reCAPTCHA
const recaptchaVerifier = new RecaptchaVerifier(auth, 'recaptcha-container', {
  size: 'normal',
});

// Send SMS
const confirmationResult = await signInWithPhoneNumber(
  auth,
  '+15551234567',
  recaptchaVerifier
);

// Verify the code entered by user
const { user } = await confirmationResult.confirm('123456');
console.log('Phone user:', user.uid);
```

## Anonymous Auth

```typescript
import { signInAnonymously } from 'firebase/auth';

const { user } = await signInAnonymously(auth);
console.log('Anonymous user:', user.uid, 'isAnonymous:', user.isAnonymous);
// Later: link with a permanent account via linkWithCredential()
```

## onAuthStateChanged Listener

```typescript
import { onAuthStateChanged } from 'firebase/auth';

const unsubscribe = onAuthStateChanged(auth, (user) => {
  if (user) {
    console.log('User signed in:', user.uid, user.email);
  } else {
    console.log('User signed out');
  }
});
// Call unsubscribe() to stop listening
```

## Getting Current User and ID Token

```typescript
const user = auth.currentUser;
if (user) {
  const idToken = await user.getIdToken();
  console.log('ID Token:', idToken);

  // Force refresh if token might be stale
  const freshToken = await user.getIdToken(/* forceRefresh */ true);

  // Get token result with claims
  const tokenResult = await user.getIdTokenResult();
  console.log('Custom claims:', tokenResult.claims);
}
```

## Admin SDK: createCustomToken

```typescript
import { getAuth } from 'firebase-admin/auth';

// Mint a custom token for a uid (e.g., for custom auth systems)
const customToken = await getAuth().createCustomToken('some-uid', {
  premiumAccount: true,
});
// Send customToken to client; client calls signInWithCustomToken(auth, customToken)
```

## Admin SDK: verifyIdToken

```typescript
import { getAuth } from 'firebase-admin/auth';

try {
  const decoded = await getAuth().verifyIdToken(idTokenFromClient);
  console.log('Verified uid:', decoded.uid);
  console.log('Email:', decoded.email);
  console.log('Custom claims:', decoded);
} catch (error) {
  console.error('Invalid token:', error);
}
```

## Admin SDK: Custom Claims

```typescript
import { getAuth } from 'firebase-admin/auth';

// Set custom claims (role-based access)
await getAuth().setCustomUserClaims('user-uid', {
  admin: true,
  accessLevel: 10,
});
// Claims appear in the ID token after refresh
// Client: const { claims } = await user.getIdTokenResult(true);
```

## Security Rules Integration

Firebase Security Rules use `request.auth` to gate access:

```
// Firestore rules
rules_version = '2';
service cloud.firestore {
  match /databases/{database}/documents {
    // Only authenticated users can read
    match /posts/{postId} {
      allow read: if request.auth != null;
      allow write: if request.auth.uid == resource.data.authorId;
    }

    // Custom claims for admin access
    match /admin/{document=**} {
      allow read, write: if request.auth.token.admin == true;
    }
  }
}
```

## Sign Out

```typescript
import { signOut } from 'firebase/auth';

await signOut(auth);
```

## Environment Variables

| Variable | Purpose |
|----------|----------|
| `FIREBASE_API_KEY` | Web API key from Firebase console |
| `FIREBASE_AUTH_DOMAIN` | Auth domain (projectId.firebaseapp.com) |
| `FIREBASE_PROJECT_ID` | Firebase project identifier |
| `GOOGLE_APPLICATION_CREDENTIALS` | Path to service account JSON (Admin SDK) |
